The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Hiring hope
                                                                              Tuesday , November 10 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            Hiring hope
                            
	Infosys        
	Infosys BPO, the back-office unit of Infosys Technologies, will hire 1500-2000 people by the end of the current fiscal. We plan to hire 2000 people in the next four-five months or by the end of this fiscal. At present, we are 16,000 people in India, Infosys BPO chief Amitabh Chaudhry said.              
	Barclays        
	UK-based Barclays will increase its headcount in the merchant banking segment across Asia by 10 per cent during 2010.         
	Weve seen very strong performance across Asia for all our business classes, Barclays chairman Robert A Morrice said.        
	On India, Barclay said it would continue to grow the business in the same way as it had been growing in the last five years.              
	Accenture        
	Global technology and consultancy giant Accenture will add 8,000 people in India by the end of next year, taking its employee base in the country to 50,000. We are 42,000 right now and we imagine we will be about 50,000 by the end of 2010, Accenture chairman William D Green said.              
	Microsoft         
	Microsoft India is going easy on hiring this year and will instead focus on consolidation, its country head said.                                                                                                                                       
